All Pakistan Open National Tennis Championships-2019 (Jhelum) Umer Jamshaid 11 hours ago Sat 06th April 2019 | 07:43 PM The Pakistan Tennis Federation is pleased to inform that All Pakistan Open National Tennis Championships-2019 concluded on 06th April, 2019 at the Officers services mess, Jhelum Cantonment
Islamabad (UrduPoint / Pakistan Point News - 06th Apr, 2019) The Pakistan Tennis Federation is pleased to inform that All Pakistan Open National Tennis Championships-2019 concluded on 06 th April, 2019 at theOfficers services mess,Jhelum Cantonment.
Aqeel Khan bagged the Men’s Singles title by beating Muzammil Murtaza and Sara Mansoor annexed the ladies singles title by beating Meheq Khokhar in straight sets. In the Boys/ Girls U-10 category, Hamzra Roman breezed past Abubakar Talha.
In the Men’s doubles category, Aqeel Khan pairing with Shahzad Khan overwhelmed M. Abid & M. Waqas in a well contested three set tie.
Results are as follows:
Aqeel Khan beat Muzammil Murtaza: 6-2, 7-6 (4);
Men’s Doubles Final:
Aqeel Khan/ Shahzad Khan beat M. Abid/ M. Waqas: 3-6, 6-1, 10-1;
Ladies Singles Final:
Sara Mansoor beat Meheq Khokhar: 6-4, 6-4;
Boys/ Girls U-10 Singles Final:
Hamza Roman beat Abubakar Talha: 4-1, 4-1;
